\begin_layout Description

\family sans
mosaic:

\family default
 (sometimes denoted with 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

) all raster data pertaining to a given wide-area ( e.g.
 a GeoTIFF of a defined area at a fixed time) and any associated metadata.
 The mosaic itself will be stored in object storage while 
\family sans
mosaic.metadata
\family default
 will exist in the database to avoid runaway database bloat.
 A 
\family sans
mosaic
\family default
 is the highest order object within a given data pyramid,
 with all lower order objects referring back to the source 
\family sans
mosaic
\family default
.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Description
* The naming convention,
 e.g.
 for a 
\family sans
mosaic
\family default
 taken on 
\family typewriter
DD/MM/YY
\family default
 of 
\family typewriter
Someplace,
 NA
\family default
 measured in the visible and near infrared with raster pixel type 
\family typewriter
Uint8
\family default
 will be:
 YYMMDD_som_rgbn_uint8.GeoTiff.
 (Here I will list other possible values for bands and pixel dtype)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Description

\family sans
tile.scheme:

\family default
 (herein denoted with 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau$
\end_inset

) the scheme by which the source mosaic has been subdivided.
 A scheme consists of:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\family typewriter
 (source_mosaic_id,version_num,tile_size,zoom) 
\family default
and will vary depending on the end use of the data.
 If it is for machine learning purposes,
 
\family typewriter
zoom=null
\family default
 and zoom level is disregarded and defaulted to 1.
 If the tile needs to be web-map compatible then the output will need to align with global web maps and the 
\family sans
tile.directory 
\family default
will abide by a strict z/x/y pyramid,
 with each pyramid organized under 
\family typewriter
source_mosaic_id/version_num
\family default
/.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Description
* In total there will be 
\begin_inset Formula $z\cdot x\cdot y$
\end_inset


\family sans
 
\family default
tiles generated,
 determinded by the size of the 
\family typewriter
source_mosaic
\family default
 and 
\family typewriter
tile_size
\family default
 (and whether zoom is desired or not)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Description

\family sans
tile:

\family default
 (herein denoted with 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{z/x/y}$
\end_inset

) stores the 
\begin_inset Formula $h\cdot w\cdot b$
\end_inset

 values of a subdivision of a source mosaic (with 
\begin_inset Formula $h,w$
\end_inset

 the tiles height and width and 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 the bandcount) along with any geographic data.
 These bytes are stored in
\family sans
 
\family typewriter

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

source_mosaic_id/version_num/tiles/z/x/y.tif
\family default
.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description

\family sans
tile.thumbnail:

\family default
 (herein denoted with 
\begin_inset Formula $th_{z/x/y}$
\end_inset

) each tile will also have a rgb thumbnail of a reduced dimension,
 stored parallel to 
\family sans
tile 
\family default
in object storage for lightweight visualization,
 labeling,
 and web integration tasks.
 These bytes will be stored in 
\family typewriter
source_mosaic_id/version_num/thumbs/z/x/y.<webp
\backslash
png>.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description

\family sans
tile.metadata:
 
\family default
(herein denoted with 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{t_{z/x/y}}$
\end_inset

) each tile/thumb pair stored in object storage will have its metadata stored in the database for fast lookup.
 
\end_layout

